[div class=p 
	"This is a TAS of an official promotional browser game for Donkey Kong Country 3 on the GBA.
	$LF
	"The game consists of placing the barrels in the correct place and angle so that Dixie Kong and Kiddy Kong get shot out of them without hitting any walls, and reaching the exit.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When I click on "Play!", I instantly hover the cursor over the "Click + Drag" button at the bottom. I've come to realize that a good majority of Flash games will register a click input earlier if I hover over clickable buttons/functions 1 frame before I make a click input. This is done throughout the TAS.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I let go a barrel after placing it and after waiting 1 frame I change the angle. It takes about 3 frames to properly change the angle to where I want and finally I let go. 1 frame later I grab the next barrel, and so on, so forth.
	$LF
]div
